1.title: Who's on First with Maurice LaMarche
1.plot: Rob Paulsen launches his new web series Talkin' Toons by bringing on his old buddy Maurice LaMarche, who played the Brain. Watch as Rob talks with Maurice about their time on Animaniacs and Pinky and the Brain.

2.title: Talkin' Batman w/ Kevin Conroy, Paul Dini, and Alan Burnett
2.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Kevin Conroy, Paul Dini, and Alan Burnett to discuss their work on Batman: The Animated Series and their other experience in the animation industry.

3.title: Talkin' Toons with Tara Strong
3.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Tara Strong on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Tara's start in the voice work industry and how her characters have shaped peoples' childhoods.

4.title: Talkin' Toons with Randy Rogel
4.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Randy Rogel on Talkin' Toons where they discuss their mutual experience on the hit cartoon Animaniacs and do some duets on the piano.

5.title: Talkin' Toons with Billy West
5.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Billy West on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Billy's experience on the hit series Futurama and read some scripts together as their beloved characters from their work.

6.title: Talkin' Toons with the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
6.plot: Rob Paulsen is reunited with his Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles co-stars Cam Clarke, Townsend Coleman, and Barry Gordon on Talkin' Toons where they discuss their shared experiences in voice acting and the phenomenon that TMNT has become.

7.title: Talkin' Toons with the TMNT Villains
7.plot: Rob Paulsen is reunited with some of Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles' notable villains, Pat Fraley, Renae Jacobs, and Pete Renaday, on Talkin' Toons where they discuss their experiences on the show and the icon TMNT has become.

8.title: Talkin' Toons with Matthew Mercer
8.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Matthew Mercer on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Matthew's following from Overwatch, Critical Role, and more, as well as their different experiences in the world of voice acting.

9.title: Talkin' Toons with Nolan North
9.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Nolan North on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Nolan's work in the voice acting business with characters all across the board the world of DC Comics, as well as their shared experience in the industry overall.

10.title: Talkin' Toons with Phil LaMarr
10.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Phil LaMarr on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Phil's work as Hermes on Futurama and Samurai Jack on Samurai Jack, and his acting on Mad TV, as well as their experience voice acting overall.

11.title: Talkin' Toons with Nancy Cartwright
11.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Nancy Cartwright on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Nancy's work as the legendary character of Bart Simpson on the hit TV animated series The Simpsons, as well as their shared experience as voice actors.

12.title: Talkin' Toons with Andrea Romano
12.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Andrea Romano on Talkin' Toons where they discuss their work together on Animaniacs and Pinky and the Brain, as well as Andrea's notable work as a voice director and voice actress herself.

13.title: Talkin' Toons with Dee Bradley Baker
13.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Dee Bradley Baker on Talkin' Toons where they discuss Dee's characterizations of various animals in different animated series as well as their shared experiences in the world of voice acting.

14.title: Talkin' Toons with John DiMaggio
14.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by John DiMaggio on Talkin' Toons where they discuss John's start in the industry as an actor, as well as his notable work as the character of Bender on the hit animated series Futurama.

15.title: Talkin' Toons with Taliesin Jaffe
15.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Taliesin Jaffe to discuss Taliesin's history with on and off camera work, as well as his and Rob's differing experiences in the voice acting industry.

16.title: Talkin' Toons with Alan Oppenheimer
16.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Alan Oppenheimer to discuss his illustrious career in both acting and voice over work as well as read some scripts together as some as their notable characters.

17.title: Talkin' Toons with Tom Ruegger
17.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by writer, senior producer, and creator of Animaniacs Tom Ruegger to discuss the impact that the show has made and what they've both worked on since.

18.title: Talkin' Toons with Seth Green
18.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Seth Green to discuss Seth's work in the world of voiceover, as well as his on camera work.

19.title: Talkin' Toons with Laraine Newman
19.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Laraine Newman to discuss her infamous history in the entertainment industry and what she's working on currently.

20.title: Talkin' Toons with Jeremy Shada
20.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Jeremy Shada to discuss Jeremy's notorious work in the world of voiceover and to see what he may be doing next.

21.title: Talkin' Toons with Eric Bauza
21.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Eric Bauza to discuss Eric's work in voiceover and his skills with impressions.

22.title: Talkin' Toons with Troy Baker
22.plot: Rob Paulsen is joined by Troy Baker to discuss his voiceover work with multiple characters from the DC universe, as well as his recent work on the Transformers series.

23.title: Talkin' Toons with Dave Coulier
23.plot: Rob Paulsen has a gas with longtime friend Dave Coulier (Full House, Fuller House The Real Ghostbusters, Muppet Babies) as they chat about their love of Michigan, celebrity impressions, and the importance of streaming services.

24.title: Talkin' Toons with Cary Elwes
24.plot: Legendary actor Cary Elwes (The Princess Bride, Pinky and The Brain, Batman Beyond) chats with Rob Paulsen about an unforgettable audition that took place in a grocery store.

25.title: Talkin' Toons with Charlie Adler
25.plot: Longtime friend Charlie Adler (Transformers, Cow and Chicken, Aaahh!!! Real Monsters) joins Rob Paulsen to talk about balancing risks in voice acting. Plus, they take a new spin on a tense scene from Mission: Impossible III.

26.title: Talkin' Toons with Kay Bess, Salli Saffioti, and Erika Ishii
26.plot: Rob Paulsen discusses voice acting in video games with Kay Bess (Rise of the Tomb Raider, Agents of Mayhem), Salli Saffoti (Resident Evil 4, World of Warcraft: Legion), and Erika Ishii (Dream Daddy, Battlestar Galactica: Deadlock).

27.title: Talkin' Toons with Rhys Darby
27.plot: Rob Paulsen sits down with Rhys Darby (Jake and the Never Land Pirates, Voltron) to discuss the importance of voice acting.

28.title: Talkin' Toons with Grey Griffin
28.plot: Rob Paulsen discusses the importance of voice acting with Grey Griffin (Avengers Assemble, DC Super Hero Girls).

1.title: Talkin' Toons with Sean Astin
1.plot: Rob Paulsen, one of the most accomplished and well-known voice actors of our time, sits down with various other voice actors to discuss their experiences! And yes, of course, there'll be plenty of voice acting games from script-reading to re-enacting famous film scenes with cartoon character voices.

3.title: Talkin' Toons w/ Dan Povenmire and Swampy Marsh
3.plot: Dan Povenmire and Swampy Marsh (the creators of Phineas and Ferb) join Rob Paulsen as they talk about the process of creating a show that so many people cherish.

4.title: Talkin' Toons with Leonard Maltin
4.plot: Living legend Leonard Maltin joins Rob Paulsen to talk about the history of animation.

5.title: Talkin' Toons with Danny Jacobs
5.plot: Danny Jacobs (The Penguins of Madagascar, All Hail King Julien) joins host Rob Paulsen as they talk about adapting a well-known role for a long-running series. Plus, they perform a hilarious scene from Willy Wonka.

6.title: Talkin' Toons with Jennifer Hale
6.plot: Rob Paulsen sits down with Jennifer Hale (Mass Effect, Metal Gear Solid, Metroid Prime, BioShock Infinite) to talk about her landmark career and the two take a new twist on a classic Star Wars scene.

7.title: Talkin' Toons with Bill Farmer
7.plot: Bill Farmer (Goofy) joins Rob Paulsen for the goofiest episode of Talkin' Toons. Plus, Bill and Rob read an iconic scene from The Godfather.

8.title: Talkin' Toons with Richard Horvitz
8.plot: Richard Horvitz (Invader Zim, The Angry Beavers, The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy) joins Rob Paulsen to discuss his vast career in voice acting and animation. Also, the two recreate a classic scene from Spaceballs.

9.title: Talkin' Toons with Butch Hartman
9.plot: Butch Hartman, creator of The Fairly OddParents, Danny Phantom, TUFF Puppy, and Bunsen Is a Beast, joins Rob Paulsen to discuss the storytelling process in animation. Plus, the two put a new spin on a Kirk and McCoy conversation.

10.title: Talkin' Toons with James Arnold Taylor
10.plot: James Arnold Taylor (Ratchet and Clank, Fred Flinstone, Star Wars: The Clone Wars) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about the opportunity to voice iconic roles from historic franchises.

11.title: Talkin' Toons with Carlos Alazraqui
11.plot: Rob Paulsen, one of the most accomplished and well-known voice actors of our time, sits down with various other voice actors to discuss their experiences. And yes, of course, there'll be plenty of voice acting games from script-reading to re-enacting famous film scenes with cartoon character voices.

12.title: Talkin' Toons with Jim Cummings
12.plot: Jim Cummings (Winnie the Pooh, Darkwing Duck, Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles) joins host Rob Paulsen as they chat about the real-life inspirations that influence iconic roles. Plus, the plane scene from The Dark Knight Rises has a new meaning with Tigger as Bane.

13.title: Talkin' Toons with Scott Adsit
13.plot: Scott Adsit (Big Hero 6, 30 Rock) joins host Rob Paulsen to chat about improv comedy, network television, and the different skill sets needed for script reading in animation. Also, did you ever think you'd hear Baymax as Jack from The Shining?

14.title: Talkin' Toons with Todd Haberkorn
14.plot: Todd Haberkorn (Fairy Tail, Soul Eater, D.Gray-man, Ben 10) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about the world of anime, interacting with a devoted fan base, the evolution of marketing, and making your own way in acting. And did you ever picture Grey Matter from Ben 10 and Yakko as Kirk and Khan?

15.title: Talkin' Toons with Sean Schemmel
15.plot: Sean Schemmel (Goku on Dragon Ball, Z, GT, Kai, and Super) joins host Rob Paulsen to power up and fly through Sean's career from taking an open casting call in 1999 to voicing Goku for 19 years. Also, did you ever think you'd hear Goku in South Park?

16.title: Talkin' Toons with Janet Varney
16.plot: Janet Varney (Legend of Korra) joins host Rob Paulsen as they discuss the world of voice acting, The Legend of Korra, and more. Also, did you ever picture Korra as Rey and Rob Paulsen as Mark Hamill? Well, wonder no more.

17.title: Talkin' Toons with Clancy Brown
17.plot: Clancy Brown (Spongebob, Superman: The Animated Series, Trollhunters) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about new media and the differences between on camera and voice acting. Also, did you ever picture Pinky as Dr. Strange and Gunmar as Dormammu? How about Mr. Krabs as Michael Scott and Carl Wheezer as Dwight Schrute?

18.title: Talkin' Toons with Jim Meskimen
18.plot: Jim Meskimen (ThunderCats, Avengers Assemble, Call of Duty: Black Ops II) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about creating a career using social media, technology, and the doors they open. Plus, did you ever image Tommy Lee Jones in the classic Steamed Hams scene from The Simpsons?

19.title: Talkin' Toons with Julie Nathanson
19.plot: Julie Nathanson (Far Cry 5, Suicide Squad: Hell to Pay, Lightning Returns: Final Fantasy XIII) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about breaking the mold of limiting one's self in their career. And did you ever think Carl Wheezer and Chocolina would be in the Dark Knight Rises?

20.title: Talkin' Toons with the Justice League
20.plot: Susan Eisenberg (Wonder Woman), Kevin Conroy (Batman), Michael Rosenbaum (The Flash), George Newbern (Superman), Phil LaMarr (Green Lantern), and Maria Canals-Barrera (Hawkgirl), the voices behind the Justice League, join host Rob Paulsen to discuss the Justice League reunion campaign. Also, the Justice League becomes a fellowship when they read from Lord of the Rings: Fellowship of the Ring.

21.title: Talkin' Toons with Kari Wahlgren
21.plot: Kari Wahlgren (Rick and Morty, Dorothy and the Wizard of Oz, FLCL) chats with host Rob Paulsen about going into the performing arts and talent being the determining factor in voice work. Plus, did you ever think you'd hear Haruko Haruhara as Shere Khan from the Jungle Book?

22.title: Talkin' Toons with Tom Wilson
22.plot: On a very special episode of Talkin' Toons, Tom Wilson (Back to the Future, Batman: The Animated Series, Gargoyles) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about the importance of being a storyteller and not giving up.

23.title: Talkin' Toons with Fred Tatasciore
23.plot: The talented Fred Tatasciore (Hulk, What's New, Scooby-Doo?, Trollhunters) joins host Rob Paulsen for a hilarious conversation about animation, voice work, and even an art lesson. Plus, did you ever picture characters from Trollhunters in The Princess Bride during the iconic scene between Westley and Fezzik?

24.title: Talkin' Toons with Steve Blum
24.plot: Steve Blum (Star Wars Rebels, Cowboy Bebop, Ben 10) joins host Rob Paulsen to chat about the opportunities to meet and bond with fans and how Cowboy Bebop broke through the subbing vs. dubbing barrier. Plus, Steve and Rob put a fresh spin on a classic scene between Han Solo and Jabba the Hutt.

25.title: Talkin' Toons with Mona Marshall
25.plot: The legendary Mona Marshall (Fraggle Rock, South Park) joins host Rob Paulsen as they talk about breaking into the voice acting industry, learning from Daws Butler, and becoming a puppeteer. Plus, Donatello and several residents of South Park reenact a classic scene from Ghostbusters.

26.title: Talkin' Toons with Greg Cipes
26.plot: The Beast Boy himself, Greg Cipes (Teen Titans, TMNT, Ben 10) joins host Rob Paulsen as the two talk about being turtles together, voicing characters for generations, loving one's life, and even have a jam session. Plus, did you ever imagine Beast Boy as Agent Utah from Point Break?

27.title: Talkin' Toons with Kimberly Brooks
27.plot: Kimberly Brooks (Voltron: Legendary Defender, Stephen Universe, Mass Effect) joins Rob Paulson to talk all things Voltron, Princess Allura, and how the series has changed over the years. Plus, did you ever think Pinky and Princess Allura would be in Top Gun?

28.title: Talkin' Toons Live with Maurice LeMarche & Randy Rogel
28.plot: Rob Paulsen, one of the most accomplished and well-known voice actors of our time (Animaniacs, TMNT, Rick and Morty, and many more), is joined by Maurice LaMarche (Pinky and the Brain, Futurama) and Randy Rogel (songwriter and composer for Animaniacs) to talk about the world of Animaniacs, sing classic hits, and premiere new music. Stick around after for a meet and greet with Rob, Maurice, and Randy.

29.title: Talkin' Toons with Josh Keaton
29.plot: Josh Keaton (Voltron: Legendary Defender, The Spectacular Spider-Man, Hercules) joins host Rob Paulsen to talk about reprising Shiro on Voltron: Legendary Defender and his history with the series. And did you ever plan on hearing Shiro in Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid?
